<exercise checkit-seed="0006" checkit-slug="P2" checkit-title="Probability with Or/Not">
    <statement>
        <p>
            
                <p>
                    A board is laid out in a grid. The top is broken into columns, labeled A to G, and the side is broken into rows, labeled 1 to 11. If you pick a spot on the board at random, what is the probability that the spot
                    <ol>
                        <li> is in columns C to G or is in rows 7 to 9? </li>
                        <li> is not in columns C to G? </li>
                    </ol>
                </p>
        </p>
    </statement>
    <answer>
        <p>
            
                <p>
                    <ol>
                        <li> The probability that the spot is in columns C to G or is in rows 7 to 9 is <me>\frac{5}{7} + \frac{3}{11} - \frac{15}{77} = \cdots = \frac{61}{77}</me> </li>
                        <li> The probability that the spot is not in columns C to G is <me>1 - \frac{5}{7} = \cdots = \frac{2}{7}</me></li>
                    </ol>
                </p>
        </p>
    </answer>
</exercise>
